<br>
If they want to balance things, then they would need to put monks on top of the damage table above rogues.  Not just a little bit above, but a lot.  Enough damage that there is no doubt that when you have a monks in a fight, the monks are dishing out more melee than anyone else.  In the current situation, monks are only often the second-best damagers and sometimes third or lower.  With nice weapons, other classes regularly top monks.<br>
<br>
The thing is, VI doesn't want to balance things.  The entire reason for the nerf was because someone thought that leather class tanking &quot;didn't make sense&quot;.  Since when has anything in EQ ever made sense? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukhumak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/17/02 3:30:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=401.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You can leave out ..</span><hr size=1> Quote<br>
